      "full_name": "Medunitsin Nikolay Borisovich",
      "is_primary": true
    }
  ],
  "remarks": "Nikolai Medunitsin is the Director of JSC NIIP (a.k.a. Tikhomirov Scientific Research Institute of Instrument Design). JSC NIIP is a Russian military-industrial state enterprise. JSC NIIP produces medium-range anti-aircraft missile systems for the Russian ground forces, including the Buk-M1, Buk-M2E and Buk-M1-2 missile systems, as well as weapons control systems and aviation radar systems for fighter aircraft, including the MiG-31, Su-27, Su-33, Su-30MKK, Su-30MK2, Su-30MKI, Su-27SM and Su-35 aircraft, deployed by the Russian Armed Forces. Moreover, JSC NIIP is part of the Almaz-Antey concern, a Russian state-owned arms manufacturer that develops anti-aircraft defence and cruise missile systems for the Russian military.",
  "birth_info": [
    {
      "date": "1961-10-31",
